reviews.review_text: Best Sounding SBD? After giving a quick listen to each of the SBDs on Archive, I think this one might be the best.  They're all good, as is the matrix.  This one might just be a little louder, but to my ears it's seems a little more balanced and clear.  Thanks!  Great show too, btw.

Used to love this tape Listening to this show now, I wonder why I loved it so much. This soundboard copy is beautiful and overall it's a decent show with a good setlist but not too many standouts (the Morning Dew deserves mention though). They seemed to be having fun at least. The performances were peppy (for lack of a better word),the Rocky & Bullwinkle act at the start and La Bamba in the middle of Good Lovin make for at least an enjoyable listen.
La Bamba the way it was meant to be sung!  Hearing Jerry sing La Bamba was a fantastic surprise - loved it - miss him so very much, thanks for this great version.
Show of the year, excellent sound Not much more to say.  You know it, you love it.  If you've never heard it, by all that's holy, give yourself two hours and listen to it!
